	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">qtoyoda wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">and how do u erase flash?</div>
<br />With a few clicks in the programmer software and a few seconds of waiting. Much better then dealing with UV lights, which can be dangerous and need minutes to erase a chip.
<br />
<br />I do think Flash is a bit more expensive than EPROM, but it's not like you need tons of chips... Each chip can be erased and reprogrammed several thousand times. I'd use EPROMs only for permanent carts.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


