	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Flash is better then EPROM for "permenent" data as the EPROMS are made to be erased. Flash is made to be reprogrammed.
<br /> With new carts and thick electrical tape over the chips, there still will be UV rays getting in the EPROMS and erasing them.
<br />
<br />
<br /> Plus flash chips just put in the cart look better then opening it to some used EPROMS with electrical tape over them.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


