	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It takes more than 5.0 V to erase the memory cells. Modern flash chips have an onboard charge pump to make this voltage, but older parts needed a higher voltage on a separate pin. Look at the manual for the programmer to see what voltage it takes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
